name: Mount Lafayette

trails_config.name: Franconia Ridge Loop (Falling Waters/Bridle Path)
trails_config.description: New England’s iconic loop: ascend past waterfalls via Falling Waters Trail, traverse the open Franconia Ridge (Mount Lincoln and Lafayette) with constant panoramic views, then descend the Greenleaf Trail and Old Bridle Path. This hard loop is famed for its autumn foliage and stunning ridgeline vistas.
trails_config.parking_info: Lafayette Place Parking, I-93 Franconia Notch

current_conditions.ai_summary: One of New Hampshire's premier peaks, Mount Lafayette rises to 5260 feet. It is known for its rugged terrain and panoramic vistas.
risk_factors: Check local trail conditions before departing.
Start early to avoid afternoon storms.

generated_description:
The Experience

Standing at 5260 feet, Mount Lafayette is a standout peak in New Hampshire. Known for its rugged and challenging terrain, it offers a quintessential hiking experience.

The Challenge

Hikers often choose the **Franconia Ridge Loop (Falling Waters/Bridle Path)**, a **8.6 mile** route gaining significant elevation. As part of the **NH48 4000-Footers**, it draws peak-baggers from across the region.

Peak Bagging Logic

**Peak Bagging Opportunity:** Consider connecting this hike with **Mount Lincoln**, which is just 0.9 miles away. Linking these peaks is a popular way to maximize your day on the trail.
